Iran&#8217;s Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif will travel to Moscow on Friday for three-way talks with his Syrian and Russian counterparts on the situation in Syria, his ministry said.Zarif will also hold a one-to-one meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, foreign ministry spokesman Bahram Ghasemi said late Wednesday.Iran and Russia are key financial and military supporters of President Bashar al-Assad&#8217;s regime.More than 300,000 people have been killed and millions forced to flee their homes since Syria&#8217;s conflict erupted in March 2011 with protests calling for Assad&#8217;s ouster.Moscow faces growing diplomatic pressure over a Russian-backed Syrian offensive against rebel-held areas of the battleground city of Aleppo that the UN says has left hundreds dead since September 22.-AFP